Common.SpaceDescription.Common.Text:
Landmark retail space available in the heart of the vibrant and revitalized Downtown Green Bay. The former Children’s Museum space is arguably the highest profile, most prominent retail property in Downtown Green Bay. With over 130 feet of all glass frontage on Washington Street; this site will give any business a striking presence in the downtown of the third largest MSA in Wisconsin.

This property presents a rare opportunity for a business seeking a large block of retail space in Downtown Green Bay. Join the 50+ shops and 50+ restaurants that have made Downtown Green Bay a regional destination.

Convenient access to parking with 16 free parking spaces for use during business hours as well as metered spaces available in the attached parking garage.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The development will provide approximately 53,913 SF of office space, and approximately 10,768 SF of retail space. The space is able to be demised.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Founded in 1837, Delafield is located immediately off of Interstate 94 and is a mere 27 miles west of downtown Milwaukee and 52 miles east of the Capitol building in Madison. 

Downtown Delafield, with Highway C (Genesee Street) running through the middle of it, offers a rich mix of office tenants, retailers, MUH, single family housing, and coffee shops/restaurants. Outdoor enthusiasts also revel in its location, on the shores of
Nagawicka Lake and the Bark River, but also as downtown offers direct access onto the Ice Age National Scenic Trail and the Lake Country Recreation Trail. With more new construction on its way, downtown Delafield is as vibrant as ever!

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: This recently renovated(2012)Class A office space is available for sublease immediately in Old Sauk Trails office park on the Westside of Madison. Tenant has consolidated into the remainder of the building and other space in the market. The approximately 31,940 SF space is contiguous on one floor. The space features approximately 14’ exposed ceilings with spiral ductwork and unique design elements,including several glass-walled conference rooms,and a large training room with folding walls to convert to smaller conference rooms. The high-end lobby features two-story ceiling height and ability for new tenant to have a receptionist at the front door. Common area space features two-story height space with a  fireplace and casual seating areas.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: 2700 Midwest Drive is a Class A “Headquarters” quality property. The building will be available for lease in the summer of 2021. The building features high quality construction and well-maintained building systems, nicely manicured grounds, ample parking, Interstate 90 frontage/visibility, and proximity to numerous restaurants, coffee shops, hotels, and other amenities. Proximity to downtown LaCrosse offers additional amenities.
